{"conflict_recognized": 0, "processed_response": "Installing a new toilet in your bathroom can seem like an intimidating task, but with the right tools and a methodical approach, it can be done successfully. First, gather all the necessary tools and materials, including a new toilet installation kit, protective gloves, a wrench, a wax ring, adjustable pliers, and a level. It is crucial to ensure the water supply to the existing toilet is completely shut off by turning off the valve located behind the toilet or under the sink. Once this is done, flush the old toilet to empty the tank and bowl of water, then disconnect the water supply line using your adjustable pliers.

After disconnecting the line, carefully remove the toilet by unscrewing the bolts from the base and lifting the toilet off the floor—be mindful that the existing wax ring might be sticky or messy. Once the old toilet is removed, clean the flange area thoroughly and check for any potential damage or wear. Replace the wax ring on the flange, aligning it carefully to ensure a good seal. When positioning the new toilet, guide the toilet bolts through the base holes, ensuring it’s aligned correctly over the wax ring without shifting it. Press down on the toilet to secure it onto the ring and tighten the bolts, alternating sides to keep the pressure even. Be careful not to overtighten, as this can crack the porcelain.

Next, reconnect the water supply line to the toilet tank and turn the water back on, checking for any leaks as the tank fills. Adjust the water level and ensure the toilet is flushing properly. Finally, ensure the toilet is stable by lightly rocking it to check for any movement. If it wobbles, you may need to place shims under the toilet and trim them as necessary. Once everything is secure and functioning smoothly, you can seal the base with a bead of silicone caulk for a finished and polished look. It is important to double-check all connections and alignments to prevent future complications. With these steps, you have successfully installed a new toilet in your bathroom, ensuring both functionality and durability."}

